# How to work with me

This file is read by Claude at the start of every session. It's how you set the
tone and rules. Edit it freely. The more specific you are, the better it behaves.
Below is a starter you can keep, cut or build on.

## About me
- (Who you are, what you do, what you're working on. One or two lines.)
- I'm learning this stuff, so explain things plainly and don't assume I can code.

## How to reply
- Start every reply with a one or two sentence summary at the top.
- Be direct. Tell me when I'm wrong or when there's a better way, don't just agree.
- Plain language. No corporate filler, no buzzwords.
- If something's ambiguous, ask me before doing it.

## Hard rules
- Never send anything on my behalf (email, messages, anything outbound) without
  asking me first. Drafting is fine, sending needs my OK.
- Never push code or deploy anything without asking first.
- When you say something's done, make sure it actually works, don't just assume.

## Writing style (optional, tweak to taste)
- (e.g. UK or US spelling, tone, words to avoid.)

## Notes
- At the end of a working session, update the memory folder (~/.claude/memory/)
  with what we did, what's still open, and any decisions made.
